PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784911676
OL,3,CWildfires in France and Spain force
OL,4,Cmore than 70,000 people to evacuate
OL,6,FIn Spain, the national emergency means
OL,7,Fthat the nation's interior ministry,
OL,8,Fwhich controls police and security
OL,9,Fforces, has taken charge of overseeing
OL,10,Fthe firefighting efforts by Spain's
OL,11,Fregions as they struggle to battle
OL,12,Fmultiple blazes that are being fanned
OL,13,Fby a heatwave.
OL,15,FThe regional government of Madrid,
OL,16,Fwhich spans a wide area around the
OL,17,Fcapital city, said 10,000 people had
OL,18,Fbeen evacuated from different villages
OL,19,Fas multiple fires raged out of control
OL,20,Flate on Thursday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
